title: Israel increases strikes on Gaza in 'next stage of the war'
description: Israel will increase its strikes on Gaza, its military has warned, as airstrikes rained down on south Gaza, an area Israel had said would be safer.

title: Israeli soldier wounded while freeing kibbutz wants to return to frontline
description: Hands pulling the wheels on his wheelchair, a young Israeli soldier led the way into his hospital bedroom, both legs patched up after surgery for three gunshot wounds.

title: England vs South Africa: Rugby World Cup semi-final updates
Late South Africa comeback denies England Rugby World Cup final place
description: England missed out on a place in the Rugby World Cup final after a narrow defeat to holders South Africa.

title: What Hamas's release of US hostages could mean for Israel's expected ground offensive in Gaza
description: Late on Friday night, somewhere along the Gaza-Israel border, Judith and Natalie Raanan were handed over by masked Hamas gunmen into the care of the International Red Cross.

title: Gaza-Egypt crossing opened as lifesaving aid trucks allowed to enter Strip
description: A key border crossing between Gaza and Egypt opened today, allowing a trickle of desperately needed aid to flow into the besieged Palestinian territory.

title: Father of freed US hostage say she is 'doing good' following her release from Hamas captivity
description: The father of freed American hostage Natalie Raanan says she's doing well following her two weeks in captivity after she and her mother were abducted in Israel by Hamas.
